name: O.J. Simpson
summary: Former American football player O.J. Simpson has passed away at 76 after a battle with cancer. Simpson, a star athlete in the National Football League (NFL), gained notoriety after he was acquitted of the murder of his ex-wife Nicole Brown Simpson and her friend Ron Goldman in 1995. The highly publicized trial captivated the nation and sparked significant controversy. Following his acquittal, Simpson faced civil liability for the deaths and was ordered to pay damages. In recent years, Simpson had been living a relatively private life until his death was announced by celebrity news outlet TMZ.

summary: In the first round of the 2024 Masters, Bryson DeChambeau showcased his newfound form with a stellar 7-under 65, propelling him to the summit of the leaderboard and a one-stroke advantage over Scottie Scheffler. This remarkable performance marks a reversal from his previous comments questioning Augusta National's par-67 rating. DeChambeau's dominance is even more striking considering his use of 3-D printed irons, highlighting his commitment to innovation and technological advancements. His strong start has pundits and experts alike predicting a potential victory, with many identifying him as a top contender for the coveted green jacket. DeChambeau's meticulous attention to detail, including his choice of clothing and equipment, further underscores his determination to conquer Augusta National and etch his name into the annals of golf history.

name: Akebono
summary: Akebono Taro, the first foreign-born sumo grand champion, passed away at the age of 54 due to heart failure. Born in Hawaii, Akebono achieved unparalleled success in the sport, becoming the first non-Japanese wrestler to reach the highest rank of yokozuna. His legacy extends beyond sumo, as he also pursued a career in professional wrestling. Akebono's passing has left a significant void in the world of sumo and has been met with tributes from fellow wrestlers, fans, and the Japanese public, who recognized his pioneering spirit and the profound impact he had on the sport.

name: Cicadas emerge
summary: In the upcoming spring, an extraordinary natural event will unfold in several regions of the United States: a double-brood emergence of billions of periodical cicadas. This rare phenomenon occurs when two distinct broods of these insects emerge simultaneously, creating an overwhelming spectacle. Scientists have determined that the last emergence of this magnitude occurred 17 years ago, and now, Brood X and Brood XIII are poised to emerge in 2024. The emergence is expected to begin in late April or early May, with the cicadas' distinctive buzzing becoming a cacophony throughout the affected areas. Experts anticipate that up to a trillion insects could emerge, potentially covering trees, vegetation, and even buildings with their sheer numbers. This invasion will provide a unique opportunity for scientific observation and public fascination, as researchers study the cicadas' unique behaviors and the impact they have on their surroundings.

name: Arizona Coyotes
summary: The Arizona Coyotes' future in Arizona is uncertain. The team has announced a commitment to win a state land auction and build a privately funded arena and entertainment district, but there are also reports that the team could relocate to Salt Lake City as part of an NHL plan. NHL commissioner Gary Bettman has said that the league is exploring all options for the Coyotes, including sale, relocation, and expansion. The Coyotes have been struggling to find a permanent home in Arizona since moving to the state in 1996. Their current arena, Gila River Arena, is outdated and has been criticized by fans and players. The team has also been facing financial difficulties in recent years. The Coyotes' plan to build a new arena is contingent on winning the state land auction. If they are unable to do so, they could be forced to relocate. The Coyotes have also been criticized for their "tone-deaf" posts on social media amid the relocation rumors. The team has been posting photos of fans and players with the hashtag #Yotes4Ever, which has been met with backlash from fans who believe the team is not doing enough to stay in Arizona.
